@node 3.1. "Requirements"
                               @{fg highlight}@{b}@{u} 3.1. Requirements@{uu}@{fg text}@{ub}

This package needs:

o AmigaOS 2.04 / Kickstart V37 or higher.


o xpkmaster.library V4+ [INCLUDED]
(© Bryan Ford, Urban Dominik Müller, Christian von Roques, Dirk Stöcker)
@{b}( Aminet:  Util/pack/xpk_user.lha)@{ub}

Some changes were made recently in the XpkPrefsSemaphore protocol.
This release of XpkCybPrefs needs xpkmaster V4.15 or higher.
If you use an older v4 version, you may get some enforcer read-hits
(nothing to worry about). Also, some new features like the "USERefficiency"
criterion won't work.
[Unfortunately, semaphore version can't be tested]


o Reqtools.library (© Nico Francois) [everybody has this one eh...]


o datamaster.library package (© Alexis Nasr ;-) [INCLUDED]
@{b}( Aminet:  Util/Libs/Datamaster_lib.lha)@{ub}



@ENDNODE

@node 3.2. "Installation"
                               @{fg highlight}@{b}@{u} 3.2. Installation@{uu}@{fg text}@{ub}

* XpkCybPrefs would usually be put in your SYS:WBStartup directory.

* The XpkCyb.prefs config file goes in ENV: & ENVARC:

* datamaster.library, its "recognizers", and DMcontrol are provided.

   copy contents of:            "libs" directory to LIBS:
                                "c"    directory to C:

Complete archive of datamaster on aminet:  @{b}Util/Libs/Datamaster_lib.lha@{ub}

I strongly advise you to get the full archive, that provides complete docs
(user & programmer), and associated utilities such as DMcontrol and
DMlauncher. [end of the advert :]

* I also included current version of xpkmaster at the moment of the
release, so you can have a quickstart (but getting the complete lastest
archive is of course recommended)


@ENDNODE

